New approved policies - plus your chance to have your say

There are 40 policy documents currently being reviewed across the Universit=
y. Not all are policies, some are procedures and others are guidelines, but=
 all are available for input from both staff and students.=0D
=0D
Have your say in these reviews here: http://www.mq.edu.au/policy/under_revi=
ew.html=0D
=0D
Of specific interest might be the discussion around the development of a dr=
aft Grading Policy. This has highlighted the need for discussion on the use=
 and relevance of SNGs (Standardised Numerical Grades) and when (or if) a P=
C grade should be awarded. If you have a specific view or would like to rec=
eive a copy of the draft document, please contact Associate Professor Pamel=
a Coutts at pamela.coutts@mq.edu.au=0D
=0D
